10:31.371 --> 10:33.872
Okay, what is she hiding?

10:33.874 --> 10:35.774
I'll tell you in a minute.

10:35.776 --> 10:39.344
I want to enjoy the suspense
a little bit first.

10:40.313 --> 10:42.481
Ooh.

10:49.927 --> 10:52.695
Oh, my God, will
you just tell us!

10:55.032 --> 10:56.699
Very well.

10:56.701 --> 10:57.934
Now, we can all agree

10:57.936 --> 11:00.537
that this is the first
time I've ever set foot

11:00.539 --> 11:02.005
in this house, correct?

11:02.007 --> 11:04.207
Oh, this is
going to be unbearable.

11:04.209 --> 11:06.142
Now, Captain, your powder room--

11:06.144 --> 11:08.778
does it face out
on the ocean?

11:08.780 --> 11:10.880
Of course, right over the cliff.

11:10.882 --> 11:12.048
Just as I suspected.

11:12.050 --> 11:13.449
And if I were to walk

11:13.451 --> 11:15.351
into this powder
room right now,

11:15.353 --> 11:17.854
I believe I'd see a
potted plant of some sort.

11:17.856 --> 11:19.055
Is that correct?

11:19.057 --> 11:21.057
Yes. There's a daisy.

11:21.059 --> 11:23.359
A daisy. Interesting.

11:23.361 --> 11:25.929
Uh, not traditionally
an indoor plant,

11:25.931 --> 11:29.032
but I suppose
it gets plenty of light

11:29.034 --> 11:30.833
with the southern exposure.

11:30.835 --> 11:32.569
That's right, it does.

11:32.571 --> 11:34.904
Will you please fetch the daisy?

11:34.906 --> 11:37.140
Aye-aye.

11:38.409 --> 11:39.809
I totally solved it.

11:39.811 --> 11:41.177
You didn't solve it.

11:41.946 --> 11:43.880
You didn't solve it.

11:43.882 --> 11:45.081
You didn't
solve it.

11:45.083 --> 11:46.583
You didn't solve it.

11:46.585 --> 11:48.585
Did you solve...?
No, you didn't solve it.

11:48.587 --> 11:50.386
I solved it!

11:50.388 --> 11:51.821
Ah.

11:51.823 --> 11:53.590
Thank you, Captain.

11:53.592 --> 11:55.625
Now...

11:55.627 --> 11:57.760
a simple question.

11:57.762 --> 12:01.230
When Lily and Marshall are apart
for an extended period of time,

12:01.232 --> 12:04.934
what is the one thing
Lily always does?

12:04.936 --> 12:05.935
Cry?

12:05.937 --> 12:07.170
Masturbate?

12:07.172 --> 12:08.037
Karate?

12:08.039 --> 12:09.105
Go sailing?

12:09.107 --> 12:11.107
No.

12:11.109 --> 12:13.376
When Lily and Marshall are apart

12:13.378 --> 12:16.879
for a long period of time,

12:16.881 --> 12:20.483
Lily... always...

12:28.292 --> 12:30.693
...starts smoking again.

12:31.495 --> 12:33.363
That's true, she does.

12:33.365 --> 12:35.398
Happened when she went
to Paris in college.

12:35.400 --> 12:38.501
It happened when she moved
to San Francisco, and last week,

12:38.503 --> 12:40.370
<i>it happened again.</i>

12:40.372 --> 12:42.705
<i>From the moment Marshall left</i>
<i>for Minnesota,</i>

12:42.707 --> 12:44.641
<i>Lily's been secretly</i>
<i>puffing down the ciggies</i>

12:44.643 --> 12:47.610
<i>like a 46-year-old grandma</i>
<i>at a Reno slot machine.</i>

12:47.612 --> 12:49.812
<i>Problem was,</i>
<i>come Friday morning,</i>

12:49.814 --> 12:53.049
<i>she knew she'd have</i>
<i>to quit again,cold turkey.</i>

12:53.051 --> 12:54.851
<i>And it wouldn't be easy.</i>

12:54.853 --> 12:56.886
<i>She tried to make it</i>
<i>a whole car ride</i>

12:56.888 --> 12:58.154
<i>without a fix, but couldn't.</i>

12:58.156 --> 12:59.822
So, she pretended to be annoyed

12:59.824 --> 13:02.759
by perfectly reasonable things,
<i>like my stylish driving gloves</i>

13:02.761 --> 13:06.396
<i>and my appreciation of the</i>
<i>historic van Otterloop manse.</i>

13:06.398 --> 13:11.934
<i>All so she could have</i>
<i>one last smoke on the train.</i>

13:11.936 --> 13:14.237
<i>But afterwards,</i>
<i>her breath told the tale.</i>

13:14.239 --> 13:17.573
<i>And that's why,</i>
<i>when she got to the hotel,</i>

13:17.575 --> 13:19.509
<i>Lily...</i>

13:19.511 --> 13:22.578
<i>was chewing... gum.</i>

13:22.580 --> 13:23.780
Lily never chews gum.

13:23.782 --> 13:24.681
What? Never?

13:24.683 --> 13:25.748
Well, hardly ever.

13:25.750 --> 13:27.283
Great job, Ted.

13:27.285 --> 13:29.986
That's some pretty
solid evidence. Gum.

13:29.988 --> 13:33.456
(laughing):
Oh, Barney, my dear boy.

13:33.458 --> 13:35.058
I'm just getting started.

13:35.060 --> 13:36.459
Getting started?

13:36.461 --> 13:37.593
TED:
<i>Lily knew that cigarette</i>

13:37.595 --> 13:38.995
<i>was probably her last</i>
<i>for a while.</i>

13:38.997 --> 13:41.097
<i>She needed something</i>
<i>to keep her nerves calm,</i>

13:41.099 --> 13:42.732
<i>so she headed to the bar.</i>

13:42.734 --> 13:45.301
Anytime you see me
without a drink in my hand,

13:45.303 --> 13:47.570
you put a drink in my hand.

13:47.572 --> 13:50.273
Are you my guy, Linus?

13:50.275 --> 13:53.443
TED: <i>What followed was</i>
<i>a long day and a half for Lily.</i>

13:53.445 --> 13:55.378
<i>A really long day and a half.</i>

13:55.380 --> 13:56.913
<i>Oh, it's kind of insane</i>

13:56.915 --> 13:59.148
<i>how much happened</i>
<i>in just a day and a half.</i>

13:59.150 --> 14:00.950
<i>Anyway, Marshall returned,</i>

14:00.952 --> 14:04.387
<i>they had a big fight,</i>
<i>Lily stormed out.</i>

14:04.389 --> 14:05.555
<i>And that's when she realized,</i>

14:05.557 --> 14:07.523
<i>if she was gonna sneak one</i>
<i>this weekend,</i>

14:07.525 --> 14:08.725
<i>this was her chance.</i>

14:08.727 --> 14:11.627
<i>And after that fight,</i>
<i>boy, did she need one.</i>

14:11.629 --> 14:14.731
Only problem: she was all out.

14:14.733 --> 14:16.032
<i>Now,</i>

14:16.034 --> 14:17.166
it's 3:00 a.m.,

14:17.168 --> 14:18.367
you need a cigarette,

14:18.369 --> 14:20.069
and the only place
that's open is an EZ Pick

14:20.071 --> 14:21.370
that's five miles down the road.

14:21.372 --> 14:22.538
You have no car.

14:22.540 --> 14:24.240
What do you do? Go.

14:24.242 --> 14:25.208
Dirt-bike it.

14:25.210 --> 14:26.309
I can walk that far.

14:26.311 --> 14:27.276
Masturbate.

14:27.278 --> 14:28.277
Take a boat.

14:28.279 --> 14:30.780
What? A boat? No.

14:30.782 --> 14:33.116
Dude, she got a ride
in your car, remember?

14:33.118 --> 14:34.650
(phone ringing)

14:34.652 --> 14:35.818
Ahoy.

14:35.820 --> 14:36.786
Hi. I-I know it's late,

14:36.788 --> 14:38.187
but I've got to get out of here.

14:38.189 --> 14:40.289
I want to make
one stop first.

14:41.658 --> 14:43.760
TED:
<i>The problem was,</i>

14:43.762 --> 14:46.662
<i>Lily didn't want to smoke</i>
<i>in front of her new employer.</i>

14:46.664 --> 14:47.930
<i>So, when she arrived</i>

14:47.932 --> 14:49.899
<i>at the Captain's house,</i>
<i>there was only one</i>

14:49.901 --> 14:51.100
<i>possible course of action.</i>

14:51.102 --> 14:52.635
Can I use your powder room?

14:54.705 --> 14:56.839
TED:
<i>Now,</i>

14:56.841 --> 14:57.707
you're Lily.

14:57.709 --> 14:58.975
You've just had a cigarette

14:58.977 --> 15:00.076
in your boss's powder room.

15:00.078 --> 15:01.844
What do you do
with the cigarette butt?

15:01.846 --> 15:03.446
Throw it out the window?
Flush it?

15:03.448 --> 15:05.081
No, she-she wouldn't do
either of those things.

15:05.083 --> 15:06.382
She's an environmentalist.

15:06.384 --> 15:07.383
Stick it in your purse?

15:07.385 --> 15:08.451
Marshall could find it there.

15:08.453 --> 15:09.819
Throw it in the trash can.

15:09.821 --> 15:11.287
The Captain would
find it there.

15:11.289 --> 15:13.022
Hide it in a boat.

15:13.024 --> 15:14.957
A boat? Wait.
How would that...

15:14.959 --> 15:16.125
I don't know.

15:16.127 --> 15:18.628
I just... I like boats.

15:19.797 --> 15:21.764
No.

15:21.766 --> 15:24.167
There's only one place
that she would put it.

15:24.169 --> 15:26.102
A place where, eventually,

15:26.104 --> 15:29.438
it would decompose and serve
as a natural mulch.

15:30.240 --> 15:32.341
It's in the daisy.

15:32.343 --> 15:34.277
And sure enough,

15:34.279 --> 15:36.379
if I dig around...

15:36.381 --> 15:40.316
I am all but guaranteed
to find...

15:42.119 --> 15:43.820
A pregnancy test.

15:46.056 --> 15:47.824
You could smoke those?

15:53.997 --> 15:56.165
(vomiting)

15:57.968 --> 16:00.136
(panting)

16:02.206 --> 16:03.506
Oh, no.

16:03.508 --> 16:04.974
So, you want
the Kennedy package?

16:04.976 --> 16:06.342
Bingo.

16:08.212 --> 16:10.613
One other little thing.

16:10.615 --> 16:12.782
When you do put a drink
in my hand,

16:12.784 --> 16:14.784
let's make it non-alcoholic.

16:14.786 --> 16:17.086
There's a chance
I might be pregnant.

16:17.088 --> 16:18.454
Okay, Linus,

16:18.456 --> 16:21.224
don't start popping
the sparkling cider just yet.

16:21.226 --> 16:23.359
I'm just being cautious.

16:23.361 --> 16:25.328
I'll take a test
when I get home.

16:25.330 --> 16:27.029
It can wait.

16:27.031 --> 16:30.399
Are Marvin and I
and any other future children

16:30.401 --> 16:31.434
we may have

16:31.436 --> 16:33.703
just some consolation prize?

16:33.705 --> 16:35.905
I have to get out of here.

16:37.407 --> 16:41.010
♪

16:41.012 --> 16:43.112
(sighs)
It can't wait.

16:43.114 --> 16:43.614
♪

16:49.319 --> 16:50.253
Lily, what a lovely...

16:50.255 --> 16:52.822
Can I use your powder room?

16:52.824 --> 16:56.592
♪

16:56.594 --> 16:59.662
Two minutes. Here we go.

16:59.664 --> 17:00.164
♪

17:08.704 --> 17:11.307
Guys, we need to go back
to the hotel.

17:13.175 --> 17:15.444
Lily peed on that,
and you touched it.

17:16.512 --> 17:18.114
Lily?

17:20.284 --> 17:22.718
We're gonna have a baby?

17:25.722 --> 17:28.624
I told you guys
I could keep a secret.

17:30.460 --> 17:33.629
Uh, uh, Barney,
this-this is my mom.

17:33.631 --> 17:35.464
Hi.
Hello.

17:35.466 --> 17:36.565
Oh.

17:36.567 --> 17:37.733
Oh, he's a hugger.

17:37.735 --> 17:39.001
Nothing like your dad.

17:39.003 --> 17:40.603
(laughs)

17:40.605 --> 17:42.772
I'm sorry. I-I was
gonna tell you tonight.

17:42.774 --> 17:44.340
No. Oh, my God, no. It's fine.

17:44.342 --> 17:46.175
There's just...
there's so much we have to do.

17:46.177 --> 17:48.878
You know, we have to, um...
we have to do research on...

17:48.880 --> 17:50.813
uh, hospitals in Italy,
and we have to, uh...

17:50.815 --> 17:52.715
We're not going to Italy.

17:52.717 --> 17:54.517
Of course we are.

17:55.319 --> 17:56.552
Lily, we have to do this.

17:56.554 --> 17:57.820
You're gonna live in Rome,

17:57.822 --> 18:00.056
and you're gonna get your dream,
because...

18:00.058 --> 18:02.425
because you're giving me mine.

18:03.293 --> 18:04.860
Again.

18:04.862 --> 18:06.696
But there's gonna be
all sorts of paperwork,

18:06.698 --> 18:08.931
and-and if she's born outside
of the U.S.,

18:08.933 --> 18:10.399
she could never
become president.

18:10.401 --> 18:12.735
It's a girl?

18:12.737 --> 18:15.871
Oh. I don't know, but...

18:15.873 --> 18:18.140
in my mind,
I kind of think she is.

18:18.142 --> 18:19.241
Oh.

18:19.243 --> 18:20.876
I love you so much.

18:20.878 --> 18:23.512
Mmm.

18:23.514 --> 18:25.715
We're gonna give you
some privacy.

18:27.884 --> 18:29.952
It's my room. Why
do I have to...?

18:29.954 --> 18:31.520
Just... come on.

18:34.424 --> 18:36.359
I thought this was an exit.
No, balcony.

18:36.361 --> 18:37.660
Ah. Oh.

18:37.662 --> 18:39.729
Well, we'll just give them
a few minutes, and then...

18:39.731 --> 18:42.198
Mm-hmm.
...we'll go back in and...

18:42.200 --> 18:43.666
Oh.

18:43.668 --> 18:45.868
Oh, they are both naked.

18:45.870 --> 18:47.103
Yeah, they work fast.

18:47.105 --> 18:49.138
Yes. (sighs)

18:49.140 --> 18:51.140
Oh, darling.

18:51.142 --> 18:53.142
Oh, you're going
to be fine.

18:53.144 --> 18:55.244
You know, for every marriage
in the world

18:55.246 --> 18:57.480
like I had with your dad,
you know, there's...

18:57.482 --> 19:00.216
there's a marriage
like those two in there.

19:00.218 --> 19:02.518
And, oh, marriage is...

19:02.520 --> 19:03.786
Oh, it's terrifying.

19:03.788 --> 19:05.287
It's-it's like flying.

19:05.289 --> 19:08.457
You know, you're-you're filled
with this mortal dread,

19:08.459 --> 19:11.060
but if you find someone
you feel safe with,

19:11.062 --> 19:14.263
it's like flying!

19:14.265 --> 19:18.367
But if you got someone that you
feel is really there for you,

19:18.369 --> 19:20.636
someone you can depend on,

19:20.638 --> 19:22.938
you're gonna be fine.

19:22.940 --> 19:24.840
Do you have someone
like that?

